events.technicalAdvice: Planting area layout to be ready and necessary fencing to be done

events.name: Tractor Work for Land leveing & 1st  Ploughing - 2times
events.technicalAdvice: Land leveling one day and one day for ploughing

events.name: EnrichedFarm yard manure - Sourcing and Enriching with Microorganisms & 2nd ploughing - 2 times
events.technicalAdvice: FYM should be procured and enriched 15 days before applying. Spread the FYM and plough the land 2 times

events.name: Multigrain Seed sowing and rotavate
events.technicalAdvice: Apply Multigrain (25kg per acre) and rotavate the soil

events.name: Seed Procurement
events.technicalAdvice: Source frrom Authentic Seed producer

events.name: Seed Treatment
events.technicalAdvice: Use Panchagavya / naphthalene acetic acid (NAA) to soak seed for 24 hours before planting in the nursery bag/ tray

events.name: Seedling preparation at Nursery
events.period: Between 40 day and 50 days, the seedlings will be ready for plantation
events.technicalAdvice:
Seeds should sown at 1 cm depth in the black poly bag of filled with prepared growing medium (one seed per poly bags) after soaked in the e solution for 24 hours, washed and then placed in petri plates
with moist filter paper. All the poly bags were then kept under poly tunnel. Light irrigation wil be given with rosecan after sowing. The poly bags should be lightly watered daily with rose can up to germination. Regular watering, weeding and application of pest control and
growth promoter will be carried out to get healthy seedlings.

events.name: Multigrain Plough
events.technicalAdvice: Multigrains should be ploughed and mixed with soil

events.name: Bio input preparation
events.technicalAdvice: Preparation / procuring required bioinputs, biofertilizers and biopesticieds

events.name: Furrows and Bed Preparation
events.period: 5 days to prepare Beds and Furrows
events.technicalAdvice: The land should be divided for Papaya planting and Vegetable cultivation. 2ft for bed for Tree plantation, 1 ft space and 4 ft bed for vegetable and 1 ft space for next 2 ft bed to be done

events.name: Irrigation system
events.period: 5 to 12 days for setting up Irrigagtion system
events.technicalAdvice: Irrigation layout, water storage facility to be planned before starting work

events.name: Marking the space for trees and vegetables and make a hole and apply FYM/ Vermicompost
events.period: 2 days to mark the field and digging for tree plantation
events.technicalAdvice: Make a 1.5 cupic feet pit and fill with enriched vermicompost and keep it ready for planting at least two days before planting

events.name: Transplanting the Papaya Seedlings
events.period: Plantation will be start and depending upon the space, it will be done withing 5 to 10 days
events.technicalAdvice: Take the seedlings out of poly bag and plant it in the respective pits. 8ft between two papaya in a row should be followed

events.name: Irrigation
events.technicalAdvice: Immediately after planting the seedlings

events.name: Soil test
events.period: One day Soil will be taken from the field and given for soil test
events.technicalAdvice: Soil shoud be taken before start the land preparation activity

events.name: Land Marking
events.period: 10 day Demarking the area of planting and Fencing work
events.technicalAdvice: Planting area layout to be ready and necessary fencing to be done

events.name: Tractor Work for Land leveing & 1st  Ploughing - 2times
events.technicalAdvice: Land leveling one day and one day for ploughing

events.name: EnrichedFarm yard manure - Sourcing and Enriching with Microorganisms & 2nd ploughing - 2 times
events.technicalAdvice: FYM should be procured and enriched 15 days before applying. Spread the FYM and plough the land 2 times

events.name: Multigrain Seed sowing and rotavate
events.technicalAdvice: Apply Multigrain (25kg per acre) and rotavate the soil

events.name: Seed Procurement
events.technicalAdvice: Source frrom Authentic Seed producer

events.name: Seed Treatment
events.technicalAdvice: Use Panchagavya / naphthalene acetic acid (NAA) to soak seed for 24 hours before planting in the nursery bag/ tray

events.name: Seedling preparation at Nursery
events.period: Between 40 day and 50 days, the seedlings will be ready for plantation
events.technicalAdvice:
Seeds should sown at 1 cm depth in the black poly bag of filled with prepared growing medium (one seed per poly bags) after soaked in the e solution for 24 hours, washed and then placed in petri plates
with moist filter paper. All the poly bags were then kept under poly tunnel. Light irrigation wil be given with rosecan after sowing. The poly bags should be lightly watered daily with rose can up to germination. Regular watering, weeding and application of pest control and
growth promoter will be carried out to get healthy seedlings.

events.name: Multigrain Plough
events.technicalAdvice: Multigrains should be ploughed and mixed with soil

events.name: Bio input preparation
events.technicalAdvice: Preparation / procuring required bioinputs, biofertilizers and biopesticieds

events.name: Furrows and Bed Preparation
events.period: 5 days to prepare Beds and Furrows
events.technicalAdvice: The land should be divided for Papaya planting and Vegetable cultivation. 2ft for bed for Tree plantation, 1 ft space and 4 ft bed for vegetable and 1 ft space for next 2 ft bed to be done

events.name: Irrigation system
events.period: 5 to 12 days for setting up Irrigagtion system
events.technicalAdvice: Irrigation layout, water storage facility to be planned before starting work

events.name: Marking the space for trees and vegetables and make a hole and apply FYM/ Vermicompost
events.period: 2 days to mark the field and digging for tree plantation
events.technicalAdvice: Make a 1.5 cupic feet pit and fill with enriched vermicompost and keep it ready for planting at least two days before planting

events.name: Transplanting the Papaya Seedlings
events.period: Plantation will be start and depending upon the space, it will be done withing 5 to 10 days
events.technicalAdvice: Take the seedlings out of poly bag and plant it in the respective pits. 8ft between two papaya in a row should be followed

events.name: Irrigation
events.technicalAdvice: Immediately after planting the seedlings
